<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1136,1935,1898,2282]" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">
Definition as for genus. The specific epithet was derived from the Latin noun 
<emphasis box="[1699,1775,1997,2033]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">aqua</emphasis>
, meaning water. Thus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brock &amp; Freeze" authorityYear="1969" box="[1361,1555,2039,2075]" class="Deinococci" family="Thermaceae" genus="Thermus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Thermales" pageId="6" pageNumber="295" phylum="Deinococcus-thermus" rank="species" species="aquaticus">
<emphasis box="[1361,1384,2039,2075]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1409,1555,2039,2075]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">aquaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an aquatic thermophile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
